<br>
As far as gear goes, the ONLY stat you should worry about right now is WIS (and maybe MANA).  For casters, stats are really meaningless until you approach 50.  Unless, as a druid, you want to porcupine a lot, then AC, STR, HP, AGI, etc become more important.<br>
<br>
There are several WIS items that are relatively cheap to get.  Gold Jasper earrings, plat or velium jasper rings, and plat or velium ruby veil are all player made and add a decent amount of WIS.  Just buy them as you save up the cash.<br>
<br>
You can do the Testament of Vanear quest out of Qeynos (or Erudin?  check allakhazam's), +10 WIS, +10 MANA, soloable at your level.<br>
<br>
Once you get to, or at least near, 200 WIS, THEN start replacing items to improve AC, HP, resists, etc.<br>
<br>
Of course, with tonight's patch, many items are getting focus effects added, so it's hard to say what will happen to the prices, or degree of camping for, those items.<br>
<br>
And don't get frustrated.  I had about 145 WIS at level 30, and was able to play just fine.  Didn't hit 200 WIS until about level 47 or 48.  Take your time, it will come =)<br>
